title: For Sale:  Attention veterans: don't get ripped off by a ccw instructor. Read this
postcontent: In case you did not know, if you are an honorably discharged veteran within the past 6 years you are NOT required to take a ccw course. I have talked to at least 6 ccw instructors on here and they all told me the same thing; " you are required to take the course still". Well no your not all you need is an honorable discharge, a DD214, the ccw application from online, a67 dollar money order, and 1 passport picture. take it all to your local sheriffs department. (Call first for an appointment) Don't listen to these scumbags on here when they tell you that you still have to take it because they just want your money. I hope this helps you and saves you some money. Thanks for your service.

No additional steps are required to activate the lasergrip, so you can continue to shoot instinctively. Reliable, durable, precise windage and elevation calibration ensures accurate sighting. 

Rubber Overmolded Lasergrips are based on the same super-quick and efficient sighting principals as the original lasergrips with the added comfort and recoil control of soft rubber overmolded construction.

title: For Trade:  PSE MACH 10 Bow and Accessories
postcontent:
Up for trade...extremely well cared for PSE Mach 10 bow.  This bow was hunted with twice and has been indoors and taken care the rest of the time.  The PSE Mach 10 is a few years old but still in like new condition.  The Mach 10 was  one of PSE's premiere pro shop bows and with included parts such as sight, quiver, stabilizer was over $1400.

  It will come with six high quality carbon arrows and 7 broadheads including Muzzy and Magnus (if I remember correctly), attachable quiver,  4 fiber optic pin Cobra sight, stabilizer (I believe it's a LimbSaver but I'm not sure but I do know it's a high end model),  camo soft bow bag, wrist strap.  This bow has a few years on it but extremely low use and very high quality.  The bow is completely ready for hunting, however, I would recommend a new string just to safe. She's got good speed and enough power to hunt anything that walks.  

Let's face it, high quality archery equipment is extremely expensive so buying a used but, well cared for high quality bow is the only option for shooters on a budget.  This bow was the best of the best during it's time so you're getting an excellent setup right off the bat.  

 You'll often see PSE Nova or Fireflite bows for sale on here for the same price I'm asking but the Nova or Fireflite, while being ok bows they were also PSE's base models which mean they were no where close to PSE's Pro Shop Mach series bows such as the Mach 10.  If you are going to invest in a used bow buying the best available in your price range makes the best sense, there is much truth in the fact that there is a wide disparity of quality in bows.  You can be assured with the Mach 10 you are getting a bow that was the very best available when it was released.

29" Adjustable Draw Length
70# Max Draw Weight

FtF OKC area only please.

I'll set the trade value at $400 so trades in that area will be considered.
